            <abstract>
                <p>The work is a versified retelling of the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3530OldTes">Old Testament</ref>, the Little Gospel (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT2051Nagara">Nagara Māryām</ref>), and the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2072NewTes">New Testament</ref> preserved in two lavishly illustrated volumes donated by ʾIyāsu II to the church of Dabra Bǝrhān Śǝllāse. It begins with a prose incipit: “በስመ፡ … ንዌጥን፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወንጽሕፍ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ መድበል፡ ዘበትርጓሜሁ፡ ጉባኤ፡ ምሥጢራተ፡ ዘመናት፡ ዘገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በበ፡ ጊዜሁ፡ ቅድመ፡ በዘመነ፡ ብሉይ፡ እስከ፡ ይመጽእ፡ ዘመነ፡ ሐዲስ፡.” The first volume covers the Old Testament and Little Gospel and the second covers the New Testament.</p>
                
